  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 low-confidence honest documentation)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out or not-applicable (acceptable at MRL 2). Evidence confidence is explicitly ~50% across several factors due to limited experimental replicates and wide uncertainty bounds on hemolysis model coefficients; these limitations are documented honestly with supporting rationale. The assurance team accepts the package at Medium assurance level, treating the documented uncertainty as residual risk commensurate with the MRL 2 classification and the availability of bench-test confirmation data.",
